[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/roman_key_card"]
[Student "S"]
{The chances of a slam on this hand are very small, and if WEST decides to use RKCB it will 
just confuse matters when EAST shows two Key Cards.

WEST has a better way to find out about the hand. She bids 2NT asking EAST to further describe 
his hand. EAST should then bid 3NT, showing a solid suit headed by AKQ.

EAST cannot have as much as an extra Jack, so WEST just passes 3NT.}

